---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Activity Logging & Real-time SignalR Hub - Abaki">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
        <a href="/abaki-overview" class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">
            <span class="mr-2">&larr;</span>
            Back to Abaki Overview
        </a>

        <article>
            <header class="mb-12">
                <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-white">
                    Activity Logging & Real-time SignalR Hub
                </h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
                    Implementing structured logging with Serilog and real-time WebSocket communication via SignalR
                </p>
            </header>

            <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Overview</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        Observability is critical in production systems. This module implements two complementary logging strategies:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="text-gray-300 space-y-2 mt-3">
                        <li><strong>Structured Logging (Serilog):</strong> All application events are logged to rotating files with 
                        timestamps, severity levels, and contextual information for debugging and auditing.</li>
                        <li><strong>Activity Tracking:</strong> Key business events (repo added, webhook triggered, code scanned) 
                        are stored in the database for user-facing activity feeds and audit trails.</li>
                        <li><strong>Real-time Updates (SignalR):</strong> Clients receive live updates via WebSocket as operations complete, 
                        enabling responsive user interfaces.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Learning Journey</h2>
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">📝 Challenge 1: Structured Logging</h3>
                            <p>
                                Console.WriteLine is fine for development, but production needs proper logging. Serilog introduces 
                                structured logging where events have typed properties, enabling powerful filtering and analysis. 
                                Initially confusing, but incredibly powerful once understood.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">💾 Challenge 2: Log File Management</h3>
                            <p>
                                Log files grow quickly. Serilog's rolling interval and file size limits prevent disk space issues. 
                                Configured monthly rolling with size limits to keep the most recent logs easily accessible.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">🔌 Challenge 3: SignalR Integration</h3>
                            <p>
                                WebSockets are powerful but require careful resource management. Learned about hubs, connection 
                                handling, groups, and broadcasting. The biggest lesson: ensure proper cleanup of connections to 
                                prevent memory leaks.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">📊 Challenge 4: Real-time vs. Persistent</h3>
                            <p>
                                Some logs should be persistent (audit trails), others should be real-time ephemeral updates (live 
                                status). Learned to use the right tool for each: database for audit trails, SignalR for real-time.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">✅ Key Learning</h3>
                            <p>
                                Logging is not a feature, it's infrastructure. Good logging saves hours during debugging and provides 
                                audit trails for compliance. Real-time updates make applications feel responsive.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Key Code Implementation</h2>
                    
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">Serilog Configuration</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// Program.cs - Serilog Setup
var logPath = Path.Combine(builder.Environment.ContentRootPath, "Logs");
Directory.CreateDirectory(logPath);

Log.Logger = new LoggerConfiguration()
    // Set minimum severity level
    .MinimumLevel.Information()
    
    // Override specific namespaces to reduce noise
    .MinimumLevel.Override("Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore", LogEventLevel.Warning)
    
    // File sink with rolling interval
    .WriteTo.File(
        path: Path.Combine(logPath, "Log-.txt"),
        outputTemplate: "[{Timestamp:yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss} {Level:u3}] {Message:lj}{NewLine}{Exception}",
        rollingInterval: RollingInterval.Month,  // New file each month
        rollOnFileSizeLimit: true,               // New file when size exceeds limit
        retainedFileCountLimit: 12               // Keep last 12 files (~1 year)
    )
    
    // Enrich logs with additional context
    .Enrich.FromLogContext()
    
    // Create logger
    .CreateLogger();

builder.Host.UseSerilog();

// In Startup, inject ILogger<T> wherever needed
// Then use: _logger.LogInformation("Event: {EventName}", eventName);
`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Serilog writes structured logs to rotating files. The rolling interval ensures old logs are automatically 
                            archived, preventing disk bloat.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">Activity Service for Database Tracking</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// Services/ActivityService.cs
public class ActivityService : IActivityService
{
    private readonly AbakiDb _db;
    private readonly ILogger<ActivityService> _logger;
    private readonly IHubContext<LogHub> _hubContext;

    public ActivityService(
        AbakiDb db,
        ILogger<ActivityService> logger,
        IHubContext<LogHub> hubContext)
    {
        _db = db;
        _logger = logger;
        _hubContext = hubContext;
    }

    public async Task LogAsync(
        int repoId,
        ActivityType type,
        string message)
    {
        _logger.LogInformation(
            "Recording activity: {Type} for repo {RepoId}",
            type,
            repoId
        );

        // Create persistent activity record
        var activity = new Activity
        {
            RepoId = repoId,
            Type = type,
            Message = message,
            Timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow
        };

        _db.Activities.Add(activity);
        await _db.SaveChangesAsync();

        // Convert to DTO for transmission
        var activityDto = new ActivityDto
        {
            Id = activity.Id,
            RepoId = activity.RepoId,
            Type = activity.Type.ToString(),
            Message = activity.Message,
            Timestamp = activity.Timestamp
        };

        // Broadcast to all connected clients
        await _hubContext.Clients.All.SendAsync("ActivityLogged", activityDto);
    }

    public async Task<List<ActivityDto>> GetActivitiesAsync(int repoId)
    {
        var activities = await _db.Activities
            .Where(a => a.RepoId == repoId)
            .OrderByDescending(a => a.Timestamp)
            .Take(100)  // Limit to recent activities
            .ToListAsync();

        return activities.Select(a => new ActivityDto
        {
            Id = a.Id,
            RepoId = a.RepoId,
            Type = a.Type.ToString(),
            Message = a.Message,
            Timestamp = a.Timestamp
        }).ToList();
    }
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Activities are saved to the database (persistent audit trail) and simultaneously broadcast via SignalR 
                            (real-time UI updates).
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">SignalR Hub for Real-time Communication</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// Hubs/LogHub.cs
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.SignalR;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

public class LogHub : Hub
{
    private readonly ILogger<LogHub> _logger;

    public LogHub(ILogger<LogHub> logger)
    {
        _logger = logger;
    }

    // Called when a client connects
    public override async Task OnConnectedAsync()
    {
        _logger.LogInformation(
            "Client connected: {ConnectionId}",
            Context.ConnectionId
        );

        await Clients.All.SendAsync("UserConnected", new
        {
            userId = Context.ConnectionId,
            timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow
        });

        await base.OnConnectedAsync();
    }

    // Called when a client disconnects
    public override async Task OnDisconnectedAsync(Exception? exception)
    {
        _logger.LogInformation(
            "Client disconnected: {ConnectionId}",
            Context.ConnectionId
        );

        if (exception != null)
            _logger.LogError(exception, "Disconnection error");

        await Clients.All.SendAsync("UserDisconnected", new
        {
            userId = Context.ConnectionId,
            timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow
        });

        await base.OnDisconnectedAsync(exception);
    }

    // Method clients can call to receive status updates
    public async Task SendStatusUpdate(string message)
    {
        _logger.LogInformation("Broadcasting status: {Message}", message);

        await Clients.All.SendAsync("StatusUpdate", new
        {
            message = message,
            timestamp = DateTime.UtcNow
        });
    }
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            The Hub is intentionally minimal. Server-to-client communication happens via hubContext.Clients.All.SendAsync() 
                            in services.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">Client-Side SignalR Connection</h3>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden">
                            <pre class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// Client JavaScript
const connection = new signalR
    .HubConnectionBuilder()
    .withUrl("/hubs/log")
    .withAutomaticReconnect()
    .build();

// Connect to server
connection.start()
    .catch(err => console.error("Connection failed:", err));

// Handle real-time activity updates
connection.on("ActivityLogged", (activity) => {
    console.log("New activity:", activity);
    updateActivityFeed(activity);
    showNotification(activity.message);
});

// Handle status updates
connection.on("StatusUpdate", (status) => {
    console.log("Status:", status.message);
    updateStatusUI(status.message);
});

// Handle connection events
connection.on("UserConnected", (user) => {
    console.log("User connected:", user.userId);
});

connection.on("UserDisconnected", (user) => {
    console.log("User disconnected:", user.userId);
});

// Handle reconnection
connection.onreconnected(connectionId => {
    console.log("Reconnected with ID:", connectionId);
    refreshActivityFeed();  // Catch up on missed events
});
`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            The client establishes a WebSocket connection and listens for real-time events from the server. 
                            Automatic reconnection handles network interruptions.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Technology Stack</h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        {['C#', 'Serilog', 'SignalR', 'WebSockets', 'ILogger<T>', 'Entity Framework Core', 'JavaScript', 'TypeScript'].map((tech) => (
                            <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-300">
                                {tech}
                            </span>
                        ))}
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Results & Impact</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        The logging and real-time system provides:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mt-3">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Comprehensive Audit Trail:</strong> Every significant operation is logged for compliance and debugging</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Responsive UI:</strong> Clients receive real-time updates without polling, improving user experience</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Production Insights:</strong> Structured logging enables filtering and analysis of application behavior</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Disk-Friendly Rotation:</strong> Automatic log rotation prevents disk space exhaustion</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Scalable Broadcasting:</strong> SignalR efficiently handles hundreds of concurrent WebSocket connections</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span><strong>Dual-Layer Logging:</strong> Files for persistence + Database for querying + WebSocket for real-time</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Best Practices Applied</h2>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">•</span>
                            <span>Structured logging with named properties for better searchability</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">•</span>
                            <span>Log levels (Information, Warning, Error) to separate signal from noise</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">•</span>
                            <span>Automatic file rotation to manage disk space</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">•</span>
                            <span>SignalR automatic reconnection for resilient WebSocket connections</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">•</span>
                            <span>Async/await throughout to prevent blocking operations</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
